qm:



List all VMs:

bash
Copy code
qm list
Start a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm start <VMID>
Stop a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm stop <VMID>
Shutdown a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm shutdown <VMID>
Suspend a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm suspend <VMID>
Resume a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm resume <VMID>
Create a new VM:

bash
Copy code
qm create <VMID> --name <VM_NAME> --memory <MEMORY_SIZE> --net0 virtio,bridge=<BRIDGE_NAME> --virtio0 <STORAGE_ID>:<SIZE>,format=qcow2
Clone a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm clone <SOURCE_VMID> <NEW_VMID> --name <NEW_VM_NAME>
Change VM settings:

bash
Copy code
qm set <VMID> --name <NEW_NAME> --memory <NEW_MEMORY_SIZE> --cores <NEW_CORES> --sockets <NEW_SOCKETS> --virtio0 <STORAGE_ID>:<NEW_SIZE>,format=qcow2
Show VM information:

bash
Copy code
qm showcmd <VMID>
Migrate VM to another node:

bash
Copy code
qm migrate <VMID> <TARGET_NODE> --online
Create a VM snapshot:

bash
Copy code
qm snapshot <VMID> <SNAPSHOT_NAME>
Rollback to a VM snapshot:

bash
Copy code
qm rollback <VMID> <SNAPSHOT_NAME>
Delete a VM snapshot:

bash
Copy code
qm delsnapshot <VMID> <SNAPSHOT_NAME>
List VM snapshots:

bash
Copy code
qm listsnapshot <VMID>
Enable VNC console for a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm vncproxy <VMID>
Attach a serial console to a VM:

bash
Copy code
qm terminal <VMID>
Create a VM backup:

bash
Copy code
qm backup <VMID> <BACKUP_NAME>
Restore a VM from backup:

bash
Copy code
qm restore <BACKUP_FILE> <TARGET_VMID>
Display VM console log:

bash
Copy code
qm log <VMID>




